Description: A pale brown clay seal: from the cord binding of some object, with an impressed inscription of Semerkhet. The surface of the clay is well preserved.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XXVIII, 72; H. R. Hall, 'Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs etc. in the British Museum: Volume 1 : Royal scarabs' (London, 1913), 288, no.2764; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.64, abb.229; see also vols. I, 142 and II, 822. n.820; 1123.
